# Roads Domain

**Canonical spec:** `.cursor/specs/isometric-geography-system.md` — §9 (road prefab selection on terrain), §10 (pathfinding cost model), §13 (manual draw, interstate, bridges, shared validation).

## Shared validation surface (§13.1)

All persistent road placement must produce a `PathTerraformPlan`, pass Phase-1 height validation where applicable, and use `Apply` / `ResolveForPath` for commit — **do not** use `ComputePathPlan` **alone** as the only placement decision (no plan object, no Phase1, no `Apply`).

**Two ways to build the plan** (both valid; see geography spec §13.1):

| Plan source | When | Notes |
|-------------|------|--------|
| `TerraformingService.ComputePathPlan` | Default land/slope/cut-through strokes | Used inside `TryPrepareFromFilteredPathList` after filtered path checks. |
| `TerraformingService.TryBuildDeckSpanOnlyWaterBridgePlan` | Manual draw with **locked lip→exit chord** over water/shore (FEAT-44) | All path cells `TerraformAction.None`; `waterBridgeTerraformRelaxation` + deck display height; avoids spurious cut-through / Phase1 failures on complex tails while the crossing core is valid. |

| Mode | Validation method | `forbidCutThrough` |
|------|-------------------|-------------------|
| Manual streets / preview | `TryPrepareLockedDeckSpanBridgePlacement` **then** `TryPrepareRoadPlacementPlanLongestValidPrefix` | `false` |
| Interstate | `TryPrepareRoadPlacementPlan` (full path) | `true` |
| AUTO streets | `TryPrepareRoadPlacementPlanLongestValidPrefix` | `false` |

## Resolver rules (§13.7)

- **A:** Elbow connectivity matches exactly two path neighbors.
- **B:** Prefab exits align with path in/out.
- **C:** Terraform wins — cut-through uses flat prefabs from plan, not live slope misread.
- **D:** Prefer offset paths avoiding hills when costs close.
- **E:** Interstate prefers straight segments.
- **F:** Bridge approach perpendicular to water; no turn on last land cells before water.

## Guardrails

- IF modifying roads → THEN call `InvalidateRoadCache()` afterward.
- IF placing bridge → THEN axis-aligned span only; no elbows on water/water-slope cells.
- IF manual draw holds a **locked water chord** (FEAT-44) → THEN prefer `TryBuildDeckSpanOnlyWaterBridgePlan` when stroke checks pass so preview/commit do not depend on cut-through `ComputePathPlan` for the wet core (spec §13.1).
- IF cut-through → THEN reject when `maxHeight - baseHeight > 1` (§13.6).
- IF slope-climb (no consecutive |Δh| > 1) → THEN use `TerraformAction.None` + `postTerraformSlopeType` — do not flatten terrain.
